description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**Please note that this vacancy is open to existing registered nurses only - if you are a student nurse, please contact the recruitment team on 0151 529 3030**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen on Ward 15 for permanent Band 5 posts, based at Aintree Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 15, is an acute inpatient nephrology ward, 24 beds, with an inpatient haemodialysis unit, consisting of 6 stations, a programmed care unit and a home haemodialysis unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are able to offer in house training for peritoneal dialysis and haemodialysis. Haemodialysis training is off site and 3 months supernumerary status&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant should be enthusiastic and hard-working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They should have excellent communication skills and be able to work as part of a team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some experience in renal Nursing but be beneficial but not essential&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Helen Maguire Ward Manager or Cheryl Marrs, Deputy ward manager on 0151 529 3521/3212&lt;/p&gt;
